CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 27, 1946, pg. 16 reads: "Weil School will be the scene of the symposium on Sunday afternoon, at which time Horace Cayton, Rei Ohley, famous authors from Chicago and New York respectively, and...Mrs. Thomasina Johnson, outstanding authority on labor for the United States Government, will discuss various problems of the South...Stanley Roberts of The Pittsburgh Courier will serve as moderator."
TitMainTitle: Exterior of A. Leo Weil Elementary School, with four people standing in foreground
